title: Jays' Donaldson, Rangers' Beltre knocked out of ALDS Game 1 with injuries
text:
Jays' Donaldson, Rangers' Beltre knocked out of ALDS Game 1 with injuries FOXSports 16 hrs ago Â© Nick Turchiaro-USA TODAY Sports Oct 8, 2015; Toronto, Ontario, CAN; Toronto Blue Jays third baseman Josh Donaldson reacts after being forced out at second base by the Texas Rangers in the fourth inning in game one of the ALDS at Rogers Centre. Mandatory Credit: Nick Turchiaro-USA TODAY Sports
The Rogers Centre has claimed two third baseman in one day.
AdChoices In Game 1 between the Texas Rangers and Toronto Blue Jays, Adrian Beltre was forced out of the game early with a back injury.
A few innings later, Blue Jays third baseman/AL MVP candidate Josh Donaldson took a knee to the head from Rangers second baseman Rougned Odor. He remained in the game, but was removed in the fifth inning for 'precautionary reasons' when Ezekial Carrera pinch-hit for him.
Needless to say, this is not a good development for either club considering how important each player is to his respective team.
This will be something to watch as the series progresses, for sure.
